close_reason: runtime defaults tests docs and host validation complete
body: "Feature spans runtime detection, fallback behavior, tests, and docs updates for Ollama-backed semantic defaults.\n\n## Detailed implementation plan\n\n1) Runtime semantic-default resolution (`pm-wn3r`)\n- Add deterministic auto-default resolution used by search runtime when explicit provider/vector settings are absent.\n- Prefer explicit user configuration first; only apply auto defaults when unset to avoid breaking existing setups.\n- Resolve an Ollama-backed provider/vector pair suitable for local execution, then keep default search mode behavior aligned (hybrid when semantic capability is present).\n- Add safe fallback so default-mode search does not hard-fail for users when auto semantic dependencies are unavailable at runtime.\n\n2) Regression coverage (`pm-9k33`)\n- Extend `tests/unit/search-command.spec.ts` to validate mode selection and fallback semantics with and without explicit config.\n- Extend provider tests to cover auto-default resolution and precedence rules.\n- Run targeted and full sandbox-safe suites to ensure no regressions for current users.\n\n3) Docs and release evidence (`pm-ptu0`)\n- Update README + ARCHITECTURE contracts to explain default behavior and precedence/fallback guardrails.\n- Add CHANGELOG entry with user impact and compatibility notes.\n- Record host-level verification evidence (Ollama available + semantic search execution checks) before close.\n\n4) Verification and closure\n- Run `pnpm build`, targeted unit suites, and full `node scripts/run-tests.mjs test`.\n- Validate semantic functionality on this Linux host with Ollama installed via reindex/search command checks.\n- Record evidence comments and close/release task -> feature -> epic once acceptance criteria are met."
